01:15:13.000 --> 01:15:17.000
Our last topic is the functions and effectiveness of conflict.

01:15:17.000 --> 01:15:20.000
The functions of conflict are considered to be

01:15:20.000 --> 01:15:22.000
1. Group formation

01:15:22.000 --> 01:15:27.000
2. Establishment and maintenance of normative and physical boundaries

01:15:27.000 --> 01:15:34.000
3. Establishment and maintenance of a relatively stable structure of inter-group and inter-group relations

01:15:34.000 --> 01:15:37.000
4. Integration and identification

01:15:37.000 --> 01:15:42.000
5. Socialization and adaptation of both individuals and groups

01:15:42.000 --> 01:15:47.000
6. Obtaining information about the surrounding social environment

01:15:47.000 --> 01:15:54.000
7. Creation and maintenance of the balance of power, in particular, power, as well as social control

01:15:54.000 --> 01:15:56.000
8. Normativity

01:15:56.000 --> 01:16:00.000
The special interest is presented by the functions of conflict,

01:16:00.000 --> 01:16:05.000
which are organically associated with the main feature of the production organization.

01:16:05.000 --> 01:16:11.000
The central features of the production organization and all its units are

01:16:11.000 --> 01:16:16.000
external purpose and formal institutionalization.

01:16:16.000 --> 01:16:22.000
It is these features that determine the leading function of organizational conflict.

01:16:22.000 --> 01:16:27.000
An organization as a tool is an analogue of a fertilized work,

01:16:27.000 --> 01:16:32.000
and an organization as a subject embodies a living labor.

01:16:32.000 --> 01:16:35.000
Therefore, the functions of conflict interaction

01:16:35.000 --> 01:16:39.000
make sense to consider from the point of view of the subject

01:16:39.000 --> 01:16:47.000
for whom this organization is primarily an organizational tool of his own activity.

01:16:48.000 --> 01:16:55.000
Such a subject can be an owner of the enterprise or a group of supporters of the main part of the stock.

01:16:55.000 --> 01:17:04.000
It should be said right away that, firstly, not every superior organization can be a subject in relation to this.

01:17:04.000 --> 01:17:09.000
Secondly, such an organization may not be unique.

01:17:09.000 --> 01:17:17.000
Thus, each of them is a subject of activity for this organization in various areas

01:17:17.000 --> 01:17:23.000
in supply and sale, in financial operations, in interaction with partners.

01:17:23.000 --> 01:17:32.000
Each of such organizations, which is a full or private functional subject for this,

01:17:32.000 --> 01:17:35.000
we will call a super-organization.

01:17:35.000 --> 01:17:41.000
From this point of view, every organization is simultaneously a super-organization

01:17:41.000 --> 01:17:48.000
for its relatively independent units that perform the functions of its tool.

01:17:48.000 --> 01:17:52.000
A super-organization, according to its formal status,

01:17:52.000 --> 01:17:58.000
should be located outside and over conflicting organizational structures,

01:17:58.000 --> 01:18:03.000
and, therefore, not to take part directly in the conflict.

01:18:03.000 --> 01:18:06.000
Often, in practice, the opposite is observed.

01:18:06.000 --> 01:18:12.000
The super-organization's leader, and therefore the super-organization as a whole,

01:18:12.000 --> 01:18:16.000
is involved in a conflict on the side of one of the opponents.

01:18:16.000 --> 01:18:24.000
Such participation equals the actual statuses of the super-organization and its subordinate organization or unit,

01:18:24.000 --> 01:18:28.000
which in any case reveals some dysfunction.

01:18:28.000 --> 01:18:34.000
Vertical conflicts, that is, conflicts on the subordinate leader's line,

01:18:34.000 --> 01:18:39.000
perform a diagnostic function for the super-organization.

01:18:39.000 --> 01:18:45.000
The emergence of a vertical conflict can be a result of dysfunction.

01:18:45.000 --> 01:18:50.000
Horizontal conflicts can also be a result of dysfunction,

01:18:50.000 --> 01:18:55.000
or, for example, their basis is the personal qualities of the employee,

01:18:55.000 --> 01:18:57.000
including the super-organization's leaders,

01:18:57.000 --> 01:19:01.000
or specific interpersonal and group interactions,

01:19:01.000 --> 01:19:08.000
which are not organizational, but develop within the organization.

01:19:08.000 --> 01:19:14.000
However, a significant part of horizontal conflicts in the organization are not dysfunctional,

01:19:14.000 --> 01:19:18.000
that is, they do not occur due to dysfunction and do not lead to them.

01:19:18.000 --> 01:19:22.000
Of course, the diagnosis of dysfunction in the organization is very important,

01:19:22.000 --> 01:19:25.000
but it can be carried out without a conflict.

01:19:25.000 --> 01:19:29.000
A conflict is a sharp manifestation of dysfunction.

01:19:29.000 --> 01:19:33.000
The method of detecting organizational malfunctions,

01:19:33.000 --> 01:19:37.000
designed only for the critical, acute stage of the conflict,

01:19:37.000 --> 01:19:40.000
is hardly a good basis for judging a conflict,

01:19:40.000 --> 01:19:46.000
and even more so for finding positive or positive properties for the organization in it.

01:19:46.000 --> 01:19:49.000
Next, we will turn to only horizontal conflicts,

01:19:49.000 --> 01:19:55.000
because only they can perform a function for the organization.

01:19:55.000 --> 01:20:04.000
A conflict is a interaction of objectives and objectives,

01:20:04.000 --> 01:20:08.000
since the formulation of the goal of the organization is done by people.

01:20:08.000 --> 01:20:16.000
A conflict of objectives and objectives is a conflict of possible goals and lines of organization development,

01:20:16.000 --> 01:20:21.000
and the determinants of a conflict are the representation of incompatible goals.

01:20:21.000 --> 01:20:28.000
But we are not talking about the fact that all future states are more progressive than the present ones.

01:20:28.000 --> 01:20:34.000
For example, the organization can set its main goal of preserving the existing state

01:20:34.000 --> 01:20:39.000
regardless of its public assessment or objective progressiveness.

01:20:39.000 --> 01:20:46.000
The fact that the conflict interactions of subordinates of the organization or units,

01:20:46.000 --> 01:20:50.000
which are partial goals and objectives of their activities,

01:20:50.000 --> 01:20:56.000
are an indicator not only of the pre-existing history of developed dysfunctions,

01:20:56.000 --> 01:21:02.000
but also of what can happen in the future with goals, organizations,

01:21:02.000 --> 01:21:08.000
and individual parts with funds and other components of activities.

01:21:08.000 --> 01:21:13.000
The indication of the future is the leading function of the organizational conflict.

01:21:13.000 --> 01:21:17.000
It is convenient to call it a prospective one.

01:21:17.000 --> 01:21:22.000
If the situation is recognized by the leaders of the organization,

01:21:22.000 --> 01:21:27.000
and if they have the necessary organizational funds,

01:21:27.000 --> 01:21:34.000
these leaders get the opportunity to manage the conflict or conflict situations,

01:21:34.000 --> 01:21:41.000
which will ensure the movement of subordinates of the organization and units in the right direction.

01:21:41.000 --> 01:21:47.000
The proclamation of the prospective function of the organizational conflict as a leader

01:21:47.000 --> 01:21:54.000
and recognition of the possibility of managing conflict interactions from the side of the superorganization

01:21:54.000 --> 01:22:01.000
with the help of organizational funds will give the basis for the disclosure of other functions of the organizational conflict

01:22:01.000 --> 01:22:03.000
associated with this main one.

01:22:03.000 --> 01:22:09.000
Firstly, the conflict allows to see not only the possible future of the organization,

01:22:09.000 --> 01:22:13.000
but also the ways of achieving it both in the consciousness of people

01:22:13.000 --> 01:22:19.000
and in the objectively existing environment, both physical and organizational.

01:22:19.000 --> 01:22:25.000
Secondly, the organizational conflict itself is a direct creator of the future

01:22:25.000 --> 01:22:28.000
and, first of all, of organizational norms.

01:22:28.000 --> 01:22:33.000
Here also join the socializing and adaptation functions of the conflict.

01:22:33.000 --> 01:22:39.000
Thirdly, since the prospective function separates the future from the present,

01:22:39.000 --> 01:22:46.000
it makes the organizational conflict the destroyer of the existing organizational reality,

01:22:46.000 --> 01:22:52.000
that is, the existing organizational relations, norms and values.

01:22:52.000 --> 01:22:57.000
In this quality, regardless of the benefits that the conflict will entail in the future,

01:22:57.000 --> 01:23:01.000
it causes negative attitude of the overwhelming majority of people

01:23:01.000 --> 01:23:05.000
who are under the threat of its destructive effects.

01:23:05.000 --> 01:23:10.000
It is the destructive properties, destructive abilities of the conflict

01:23:10.000 --> 01:23:15.000
that make the attempt to determine the universal effectiveness of the conflict meaningless,

01:23:15.000 --> 01:23:19.000
regardless of the opponents and the superorganization.

01:23:20.000 --> 01:23:23.000
The victory in the conflict of one of the opponents

01:23:23.000 --> 01:23:27.000
always makes the interaction ineffective for the other.

01:23:27.000 --> 01:23:36.000
In general, it doesn't matter which of the subordinates of the organization or units

01:23:36.000 --> 01:23:38.000
will win in the conflict.

01:23:38.000 --> 01:23:43.000
From the organizational point of view, the outcome that leads to the achievement of its goals

01:23:44.000 --> 01:23:49.000
and to the increase of the effectiveness of its activities.

01:23:49.000 --> 01:23:54.000
Therefore, the determination of the effectiveness of the conflict is situational in its nature

01:23:54.000 --> 01:23:59.000
and makes sense only in relation to a specific interaction.

01:23:59.000 --> 01:24:04.000
Thus, the belief of many leaders is that the conflict in the production team

01:24:04.000 --> 01:24:07.000
must be extinguished, that the work is going better

01:24:07.000 --> 01:24:10.000
and that the better the less conflicts in the organization,

01:24:10.000 --> 01:24:13.000
it has only an emotional basis.

01:24:13.000 --> 01:24:16.000
And in conclusion, I would like to say the following.

01:24:16.000 --> 01:24:21.000
Changing your attitude to conflicts practically means changing your views on life.

01:24:21.000 --> 01:24:24.000
Try to look at conflicts in a new way,

01:24:24.000 --> 01:24:29.000
and you will be able to confidently and even creatively find a way out of them.

01:24:29.000 --> 01:24:33.000
A view of a problem, including a conflict, as something positive,

01:24:33.000 --> 01:24:35.000
can be useful.

01:24:35.000 --> 01:24:41.000
It is able to transform your thinking and help you find a solution in any governance situation.

01:24:41.000 --> 01:24:43.000
Good luck!
